MetadataParser (Session utility)
monitor_prompt_counter (Session tracking)
prompts_log (Session tracking)
repo (Session reference)
report_resource_trends (Session utility)
settings (Session configuration)
technical_changes (Session tracking)
update_prompt_counter (Session utility)
updater (System utility)
updater_test (System test file)
                </pre>
            </div>

            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
<strong>Action Taken:</strong> All 32 entries were removed from the active configuration. These files did not exist on disk and appeared to be temporary resource tracking or archived content from previous development sessions.
            </p>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- UNINDEXED FILES SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="unindexed-files" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">5. Unindexed Files on Disk</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
The following 31 files exist on disk but are not indexed in the configuration system. These are legitimate documentation or system files that require addition to the configuration.
            </p>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">5.1 Priority 1 - Critical System Documentation</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
These files provide essential documentation for key system components and should be indexed immediately:
            </p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Documentation/admin/admin_guides.tt</strong> - Admin guidelines and procedures</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/DBSchemaManager_Usage_Guide.tt</strong> - Database schema management documentation</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/AI_Chat_Schema_Documentation.tt</strong> - AI Chat system schema reference</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/Result_Class_Development_Guide.tt</strong> - Development guide for result classes</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">5.2 Priority 2 - Controllers and Models Documentation</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
Application controllers and data models documentation:
            </p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Documentation/controllers/index.tt</strong> - Controllers overview</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/controllers/README.tt</strong> - Controllers documentation</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/controllers/Root.tt</strong> - Root controller documentation</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/controllers/Todo.tt</strong> - Todo controller documentation</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/controllers/User.tt</strong> - User controller documentation</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/controllers/Ve7tit.tt</strong> - Ve7tit controller documentation</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/models/index.tt</strong> - Models overview</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/models/ThemeConfig.tt</strong> - Theme configuration model</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/models/Todo.tt</strong> - Todo model documentation</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/models/User.tt</strong> - User model documentation</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">5.3 Priority 3 - Feature and Role-Based Documentation</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
Feature implementations and role-based access guides:
            </p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Documentation/features/todo_system.tt</strong> - Todo system feature documentation</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/ency/ENCYController.tt</strong> - ENCY controller documentation</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/ency/ENCYModel.tt</strong> - ENCY data model documentation</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/ency/ENCY.tt</strong> - ENCY module overview</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/proxmox/api.tt</strong> - Proxmox API documentation</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/proxmox/index.tt</strong> - Proxmox integration overview</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/roles/developer/Documentation.tt</strong> - Developer documentation controller guide</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/roles/normal/account_management.tt</strong> - User account management guide</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/roles/normal/Documentation_System.tt</strong> - Documentation system user guide</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/roles/normal/getting_started.tt</strong> - User getting started guide</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/roles/normal/mail_user_guide.tt</strong> - Email system user guide</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/roles/normal/mcoop_user_guide.tt</strong> - MCoop user guide</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/roles/user/getting_started.tt</strong> - Basic user getting started</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">5.4 Priority 4 - Configuration and Infrastructure</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
Configuration management and infrastructure documentation:
            </p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Documentation/config_based/index.tt</strong> - Configuration-based system overview</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/config/index.tt</strong> - Configuration management documentation</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/index.tt</strong> - Documentation root index</li>
                <li><strong>Documentation/session_history/OllamAssit.tt</strong> - Chat session archive</li>
            </ul>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- RECOMMENDATIONS SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="recommendations" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">6. Recommendations</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">6.1 Immediate Actions (Next Session)</h3>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>
                    <strong>Use Documentation Page Rescan Button</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Navigate to Administration → Documentation Management</li>
                        <li>Click the "Rescan" button to auto-discover and index all .tt and .md files</li>
                        <li>This will automatically add the 31 unindexed files to the configuration</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Verify Configuration Completeness</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>After rescan, verify that all 472+ files appear in the documentation system</li>
                        <li>Check that no errors appear in the documentation display</li>
                        <li>Run application tests to ensure documentation integration works correctly</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Review Role Assignments</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Verify that newly indexed files have appropriate role assignments</li>
                        <li>Ensure developer documentation is accessible to developers</li>
                        <li>Ensure user documentation is accessible to normal and user roles</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ol>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">6.2 Short-Term Improvements</h3>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>
                    <strong>Standardize File Extensions</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Audit all .md files in Documentation directory</li>
                        <li>Determine which should be converted to .tt format</li>
                        <li>Ensure consistency across the documentation system</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Establish Metadata Standards</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Define required META block fields for all new .tt files</li>
                        <li>Create standard template with proper metadata structure</li>
                        <li>Document guidelines for file authors</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Add Validation Script</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Create Perl script to verify configuration completeness vs filesystem</li>
                        <li>Generate automated report of discrepancies</li>
                        <li>Run as part of CI/CD pipeline to catch future issues</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ol>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">6.3 Long-Term Governance</h3>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>
                    <strong>Implement Auto-Scanning</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Create background process to detect new files in Documentation directory</li>
                        <li>Automatically generate configuration entries for new files</li>
                        <li>Alert administrators of unindexed files</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Create Workflow Documentation</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Document proper process for adding documentation files</li>
                        <li>Define metadata requirements for new documentation</li>
                        <li>Establish review and approval workflow</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Establish Maintenance Schedule</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Quarterly audit of documentation configuration</li>
                        <li>Annual review of file organization and categorization</li>
                        <li>Regular cleanup of deprecated or obsolete documentation</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ol>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- NEXT STEPS SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="next-steps" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">7. Next Steps</h2>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">7.1 Immediate Implementation</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <strong>Action:</strong> Use the Documentation Page "Rescan" Button
            </p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
The application's Documentation system includes a built-in "Rescan" button in the Administration section that automatically discovers and indexes all valid documentation files. This is the recommended method to add the 31 unindexed files to the configuration.
            </p>
            <div style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: 12px 0; border-radius: 4px;">
                <strong>Steps:</strong>
                <ol style="margin: 8px 0;">
                    <li>Log in as Administrator</li>
                    <li>Navigate to: Administration → Documentation Management → Manage Configuration</li>
                    <li>Click the "Rescan" button</li>
                    <li>Wait for the scan to complete (should detect all 472+ files)</li>
                    <li>Verify completion in the status message</li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">7.2 Verification Steps</h3>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>
                    <strong>Configuration Verification</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Check that configuration now contains 472+ entries (previously 440)</li>
                        <li>Verify all files from Priority 1-4 categories appear in config</li>
                        <li>Confirm no error messages in documentation system logs</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Application Testing</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Run full test suite to ensure documentation integration works</li>
                        <li>Test documentation page rendering for sample files</li>
                        <li>Verify role-based access controls work correctly</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>File Access Testing</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Test that all newly indexed files are accessible via Documentation interface</li>
                        <li>Verify that search functionality finds files across all categories</li>
                        <li>Confirm that links between documentation pages work correctly</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ol>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">7.3 Success Criteria</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
After completing the rescan and verification steps, the audit will be considered successful when:
            </p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>✅ Configuration contains 472+ entries (all files on disk indexed)</li>
                <li>✅ All 31 Priority 1-4 files are accessible in Documentation system</li>
                <li>✅ No orphaned entries exist in configuration (all reference existing files)</li>
                <li>✅ Application tests pass with documentation system</li>
                <li>✅ No errors in documentation rendering or access logs</li>
                <li>✅ Role-based access controls function correctly for all documentation</li>
            </ul>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- APPENDIX SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="appendix" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">8. Appendix: Related Documentation</h2>
            
            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">8.1 Supporting Files</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>DOCUMENTATION_CONFIG_AUDIT_SUMMARY.json</strong> - Machine-readable audit summary with detailed statistics</li>
                <li><strong>/config/documentation_config.json</strong> - Primary configuration file (source of truth)</li>
                <li><strong>Lib/Comserv/Controller/Documentation.pm</strong> - Application controller handling documentation system</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">8.2 Configuration File Format</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
The documentation configuration uses JSON format with the following structure for each entry:
            </p>
            <div style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: 12px 0; border-radius: 4px;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0; font-size: 0.85em;">
{
  "page_id": {
    "path": "Documentation/category/filename.tt",
    "title": "Page Title",
    "description": "Brief description",
    "category": "category_name",
    "roles": ["admin", "developer"],
    "format": "template",
    "site": "all",
    "last_scanned": "Thu Dec 25 2025"
  }
}
                </pre>
            </div>

            <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">8.3 File Organization Best Practices</h3>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Use .tt extension</strong> - Template Toolkit format is the standard for Documentation</li>
                <li><strong>Include META block</strong> - Every .tt file should include proper metadata</li>
                <li><strong>Organize by category</strong> - Use consistent directory structure matching configuration categories</li>
                <li><strong>Document modifications</strong> - Use PageVersion comment to track changes</li>
                <li><strong>Assign appropriate roles</strong> - Ensure files are accessible to intended audience</li>
            </ul>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CONCLUSION SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Conclusion</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
This comprehensive audit has identified and documented all significant discrepancies in the Documentation configuration system. The cleanup of missing file references (32 entries) has been completed. The remaining task—indexing 31 unindexed files—can be accomplished through a single action: using the built-in "Rescan" button in the Documentation Management interface.
            </p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
Once the rescan is completed and verified, the Documentation system will be in a fully consistent state with all 472+ files indexed and accessible. The recommendations for long-term governance will help prevent similar discrepancies in the future.
            </p>
            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

